    <div class="card">
      <h3>Americas Travel Tips</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Altitude acclimatization:</strong> Cusco (3,400m) and Lake Titicaca (3,810m) require careful acclimatization. Rest on arrival, drink plenty of water, avoid alcohol, and consult your physician about acetazolamide (Diamox) as a preventive measure.</li>
        <li><strong>Galapagos regulations:</strong> Entry requires a park fee and a licensed naturalist guide must accompany all groups. Rules around wildlife interaction are rigorously enforced — don't touch or crowd any animal.</li>
        <li><strong>Antarctica booking lead time:</strong> Antarctica cruises sell out 12–18 months in advance for popular season departures. Book early, particularly for peak January departures.</li>
        <li><strong>Yellow fever vaccination:</strong> Required or strongly recommended for many parts of South America, including Ecuador, Peru, and Brazil. Allow 10 days for the vaccine to take full effect.</li>
        <li><strong>Cuba entry requirements:</strong> Regulations for visiting Cuba vary by nationality — U.S. citizens should verify current Treasury Department guidance before booking.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

